<doc id="254749" wikidata="Q2442828" url="?curid=254749" title="Seal IV">
<text>Seal IV is the fourth studio album by Seal. It follows the aborted sessions for &quot;Togetherland&quot;, which was scrapped because Seal thought it was not up to the standard of his previous work.

In the United Kingdom, the album debuted at number four. In the United States, it debuted at number three on the US &quot;Billboard&quot; 200, making it his highest-charting album to date.

